The subfamily Cynopterinae comprises 24 species of pteropodid bats distributed exclusively in South and Southeast Asia.The subfamily contains the following genera:

Aethalops – pygmy fruit bats
Alionycteris
Balionycteris
Chironax
Cynopterus – dog-faced fruit bats or short-nosed fruit bats
Dyacopterus – Dayak fruit bats
Haplonycteris
Latidens
Megaerops
Otopteropus
Penthetor
Ptenochirus – musky fruit bats
Sphaerias
Thoopterus